      "score": 0.0,
      "raw_content": "The most common ways to say \"goodbye\" in Japanese are:\n\n1. **\u3055\u3088\u3046\u306a\u3089 (say\u014dnara)** - The standard, formal way to say goodbye. Used in most situations.\n\n2. **\u3058\u3083\u3042 (jaa)** - Casual, like \"see ya\" or \"okay then.\"\n\n3. **\u3058\u3083\u3042\u306d (jaane)** - Casual, like \"see ya later.\"\n\n4. **\u5931\u793c\u3057\u307e\u3059 (shitsurei shimasu)** - Literally \"excuse me,\" used when leaving a formal setting or meeting.\n\n5. **\u540e\u4f1a\u3057\u3088 (k\u014de shiyo)** - A mix of formal and casual, meaning \"let's meet again.\"\n\n**\u3055\u3088\u3046\u306a\u3089 (say\u014dnara)** is the most universally understood and appropriate for most situations.",
